reviewText: This is as sweet as a halmark card. (I loved the halmark store!) The story is about a man who loses his wife just as they leave the church. I would have loved to have seen the bloopers, because there were many fun actors and I'm sure that laughs weren't few. The story starts sadly and ends with a person dying for another. It's a melodrama and I loved it! It's a Thanksgiving kind of movie, but without the football players.
Title: Book Of Days

reviewText: I like Wil Wheaton. Mainly for the reasons of: Star Trek, Stand by Me, and his books and his web blog. The acting in this movie was decent. The story line was a bit unusual. Didn't have a lot of action or special effects. However it will make you think and maybe feel something. Especially if you have ever lost someone that you loved dearly. And if you ever questioned God about why.Sincerely yours,Kristy Star Sisk

reviewText: Some may not like the topics (dealing with death, bullying).  Need to choose your audience appropriately.  However, I thought it a good movie to watch.  It doesn't have all the negativity that I avoid watching on television or other media.  Can be a segment for family talks with your teens, too.
